The European Union, on Tuesday, announced a generous donation of €50 million to the Nigerian government to help in the fight against the coronavirus pandemic. The donation was disclosed when President Muhammadu Buhari received the EU Delegation, in Abuja, on Tuesday. The Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Mr. Femi Adesina, who made this public via a tweet, also quoted the Head of the EU delegation at the event, Amb Ketil Karlsen, who announced the donation, to have commended Buhari for extending the Lagos, Ogun, and Abuja lockdown. Karlsen was said to have described Buhari’s Monday natiowide broadcast as powerful, while noting that the measures were bold and necessary ones. The Presidential spokesperson tweeted, “EU gives Nigeria a grant of 50 million Euro to fight COVID-19.” This donation adds to the pool of funds available to the Federal Government in its efforts at containing the spread of the dreaded COVID-19 disease. 